      # Client

      Client¶

      xxxxxxxxxx
       
      My clients are in the sport broadcasting industry. They wish to know what are upcoming trends and so which teams and sports to focus on. Knowing which team will perform better will help them allocate TV rights to specific time, negotiating sponsorship and optimize their money allocation. My clients have are American and so a focus on USA and basketball in welcomed.

      My clients are in the sport broadcasting industry. They wish to know what are upcoming trends and so which teams and sports to focus on. Knowing which team will perform better will help them allocate TV rights to specific time, negotiating sponsorship and optimize their money allocation. My clients have are American and so a focus on USA and basketball in welcomed.

      xxxxxxxxxx
       
      # Approach

      Approach¶

      xxxxxxxxxx
       
      In order to help them, I have to check the evolution of some specific countries medal-winning progress. I have to look for specific traits in athletes that could explain performance and, ideally, using this to predict the performance of a specific team.

      In order to help them, I have to check the evolution of some specific countries medal-winning progress. I have to look for specific traits in athletes that could explain performance and, ideally, using this to predict the performance of a specific team.

      # Hypothesis

      Hypothesis¶

      xxxxxxxxxx
       
      - Athletes in their home country perform better than away.
      - Basketball gold medalists may have a height advantage.
      - Some developed countries are in remarkable athletic shape and have a steadily growing performance.

      # Discussion

      Discussion¶

      xxxxxxxxxx
       
      Further analysis would need to be conduct on the home vs away medal winning metric. The issue is that there have been only few times each country has hosted the Olympic Games, and so any inference over this is of poor quality. For example, France has been hosting the games 2 times, performing very well, but it is too few data to conclude anything. A next step could be to regroup several countries by region and checking this way, or focusing on some specific sports which would gain from having a strong fanbase around them. Indeed, in football, there's a saying that the public is the 12th member of the team, and over all the games ever recorded, there's a higher chance of winning at home, by a small but consequent margin.

      Further analysis would need to be conduct on the home vs away medal winning metric.       xxxxxxxxxx
       
      As for the basketball height analysis, it seems that being taller used to play a role in the process of winning the gold medal. However this gap persisted for several decades in the 20th century and have fallen out recently. This may have happen with an increase in competitivity and popularity of the sport, with coaches starting to optimize the recruitment and training.
      Nowadays this metric is too poor to conclude anything reliable. However, having a deeper analysis on height per role, or including other predictors may reveal interesting patterns. My metric is too general at the moment to be used.

      xxxxxxxxxx
       
      Lastly, in my focus on USA's performance accross time, I've witnessed a steady increase in the number of medals won each games. This may come from the large and varied population and the weight of the sports industry in the country. A simple linear regression revealed that the Year is, at the moment, a good predictor for the number of average medals won with quite great explanation of the variance (36% R^2). The positive coefficient attest of the increase in performance over the years. This simple model can be applied to all the countries to get a sense of possible future performance and so, I would advise my client to use this insight for future deals.

      Studying this dataset has been very interesting. As we saw, wins in Olympic Games used to be very irregular in terms of number of medal won by a country and in the physical traits of the athletes. This has however started to steady/converge the past few decades with an increase in competition and share of knowledge around the world. Getting better insights on teams and factor of success have become topics which need deeper analysis. I have put a first step in several directions which would benefit from more analysis while still showing a good grasp of the current state of the games.
